This is the Ginga Common Core Player project.

The autogen.sh script does all the magic calls to automake/autoconf and
friends that are needed to configure the compiling environment.

DEPENDENCIES
============
-> libtool  >= 1.3.4
-> autoconf >= 2.13
-> automake >= 1.4
-> directfb >= 1.0 (www.directfb.org)
-> lua >= 5.1.2 (www.lua.org)
-> telemidia-util-cpp >= 0.13.1
   (http://svn.softwarepublico.gov.br/trac/ginga/browser/telemidia-util-cpp)
-> gingacc-system (from gingacc-cpp) >= 0.13.1
   (http://svn.softwarepublico.gov.br/trac/ginga/browser/gingacc-cpp)
-> telemidia-links-cpp
   (http://svn.softwarepublico.gov.br/trac/ginga/browser/telemidia-links-cpp)

RECOMMENDED DEPENDENCIES
========================
These dependencies are optional. They provide software decoders for some types
of media, such as: Images (png, jpg...), Videos (MPEG, H264...)...
-> libpng
-> libjpg
-> xine-lib >= 1.1.7 (www.xinehq.de)
-> essential >= 20061022 (www.xinehq.de)
-> directfb-extra >= 1.0 (www.directfb.org)

INSTALLATION
============
As mentioned above, autogen.sh does all the `configure' magic.
So the installation steps are:
   $ ./autogen.sh
   $ make
   $ make install
If you need to customize any path or regular `configure' value, please
refer to the INSTALL file.
